```css
@echo off
set today=%date:~10,4%-%date:~4,2%-%date:~7,2%_%time:~0,2%-%time:~3,2%-%time:~6,2%
"C:\Program Files\7-Zip\7z.exe" a -tzip "%today%.zip" C:\SVNRepos\Sandbox\*
net use X: \\lidsrv007.devnet.local\Releases
copy "%today%.zip" X:\
net use X: /delete
```
Note the `C:\SVNRepos\Sandbox\*` option in the `7z.exe` command. This tells 7-Zip to include files from the archive with a path that starts with `C:\SVNRepos\Sandbox\`. The `-xr` option that was previously used to exclude files has been removed, as we now want to include only the `Sandbox` subfolder.<|>USER: But i meant all files in "C:\SVNRepos" but only the subfolder named "Sandbox", no other folders ASSISTANT: Understood. Here's a modified version of the batch file that zips all files in the `C:\SVNRepos` folder, excluding all subfolders except for the `Sandbox` subfolder, and copies the resulting ZIP archive to a network share located at `\\lidsrv007.devnet.local\Releases`:
