The filename of the ZIP archive is constructed using the `today` variable, which is set to the current date and time in the format `yyyy-mm-dd_hh-mm-ss`. The prefix `Sandbox_` is added to the front of the filename, resulting in a final format of `Sandbox_yyyy-mm-dd_hh-mm-ss.zip`.<|>USER: Can you also put the file in a subfolder of the share named "SVN Backup" ASSISTANT: Yes, here's a modified version of the batch file that zips all files in the `C:\SVNRepos\Sandbox` folder, prefixes the ZIP filename with `Sandbox_`, includes the date and time in the filename, and copies the resulting ZIP archive to a subfolder named `SVN Backup` located at `\\lidsrv007.devnet.local\Releases`:
